8.30	Involuntary_park	Involuntary park	Involuntary park is a neologism coined by science fiction author and environmentalist Bruce Sterling to describe previously inhabited areas that for environmental, economic or political reasons have, in Sterling's words, "lost their value for technological instrumentalism" and been allowed to return to an overgrown, feral state.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e8/Mule-deer.jpg/220px-Mule-deer.jpg
